Bertoxxxxxxxxulous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uqandow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qandow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/1/02 3:31:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14950.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A few changes coming to the forums.</span><hr size=1> As a whole, changes look great - just a little input though if I may be so bold.<br>
<br>
&quot;1. We may be moving the forums from EZboards over to PHP or another locall hosted forum script. This would mean having to bring over a lot of posts and losing all of the current titles and stuff, but we'll have a lot more control over the boards, and no advertising or donation hassles.&quot;<br>
<br>
Good move, I grow nostalgic for the old BBS style boards.<br>
<br>
&quot;2. We will be banning a few people we've been keeping track of lately. They don't add anything to the boards, and generally make the whole community look bad. A list will be posted later.&quot;<br>
<br>
Great, I will be submitting a list of maybe 40-50 candidates for banning. I would suggest that others do so as well. Let's really get this thing cleaned up.<br>
<br>
&quot;3. Graffe is stepping down from running the site. We've contacted Grimstaff, and he said he'll be happy to take over. Everyone welcome him to the new job =)&quot;<br>
<br>
About time. Was wondering if he would ever leave. Grats Grim and good luck as our new leader.<br>
<br>
&quot;4. We will be removing the spell section from the main site, it will redirect you to the Castersrealm spell list, which is much more up to date and accurate.&quot;<br>
<br>
About time you guys admitted that CastersRealm has the best info of any EQ website (although I know there are many Everlore fans out there). Actually, I think it would be nice if our members sent in a little contribution to them for maintaing their accurate spell data base as well.<br>
<br>
&quot;5. Frozboz is a new Moderator of General Discussion. His powers are in General Discussion only, to help with the influx of posts recently. Welcome Froz =)&quot;<br>
<br>
Way to go Froz! Thought I was the only one who recognized your talents. Grats and a big WOOT.<br>
<br>
&quot;6. We're going to be a lot more strict on post placement. If a post talks about balance at all, it will be moved to Class Balance. If a thread contains an form of profanity, it will be moved to Rants. This is to keep General clean and informative.&quot;<br>
<br>
Actually I'd like to offer a little constructive criticism here. The posts containing profanity should actually be moved to class balance since most of class balance discusisions do contain copious amounts of same. They would fit in nicely there. Posts mentioning balance should actually be placed in rants since you can turn into a lunatic waiting for this balancing to actually begin or continue or finish or whatever. <br>
<br>
Well just my thoughts but all in all some welcome changes on the way and just in time for the new fiscal year.<br>
